H. H. MOTTER, Collector of Internal Revenue for the District of Kansas, v. Sarah P. SNOWDEN. No. 1518. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Feb. 17, 1937. S. S. Alexander, U. S. Atty., of Topeka, Kan., for appellant. Steadman Ball, of Atchison, Kan., for appellee.

Before LEWIS, PFIILLIPS, and BRATTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellant.
